      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "Good race with a host of chances. SO MUCH SERENITY (7) has been freshened since finishing runner-up in this class at Pinjarra. Drawn ideally and will give a sight. UXORIOUS (2) is a promising galloper who placed off a wide draw on debut at Northam, then drew off the track again last time at Pinjarra so went forward and was too good. Has upside and finally draws a gate so could well make it back-to-back wins with an easier run. MYSTERIOUS FORTUNE (1) was a winner fresh then good in three runs since. Close to another success. LADY KIKI (6) is course and distance placed and looks a strong contender.",
